<br>
Soldier, very good with ranged weaponry. But not skilled at much else really. You are very dependent on weapons unless you spend some IPs to get martial arts and/or brawl up. Best weapon I have found at moment are the FA 3927 pistols. There are some nice assault rifles later on, but in the early levels the delay and damage on most other weapons is crap. Have played a soldier to 20th now.<br>
<br>
Trader, have played to 10th level now. Definitely not one of the more common professions. So far I have been able to solo, but it is definitely a lot harder than my soldier or adventurer. Decent shotgun skill if you can find a good shotgun. Nano formulas are mostly debuff skills types that transfer some of the skill to you and lifetaps. Trade skills will not really be usable till down the road, since making weapons is expensive and time consuming. Would not recommend for soloing, but a good profession if you like playing a support role in a group and like a challenge.<br>
<br>
Adventurer, one of the true generalist classes. Good with pistols and melee weapons. I currently dual wield two piercers to great affect. Has some nice nano formulas to choose from including healing, damage shields, AC buffs, and running skill buffs. Later gets to do polymorphing. Very good solo class, not great for groups since you have to generalize your skills and someone more specialized may better fill the slot. Still have a lot to offer a group though. Up to 15th as an adventurer.<br>
<br>
My recommendations...If you like melee, want to be good at soloing when need arises, and valued by a group then pick Martial Artist. Very good melee skills, can use a bow so has ranged capability unlike an enforcer, and the second best healer in the game. Very good soloing profession and has a lot to offer a group too.<br>
<br>
If you want to be the nano formula nuker from hell, go with Nano technician. You can still wear cyber armor and so have decent AC and your nukes are incredible.<br>
<br>
Just my opinion. I am still undecided as to which profession I want to play. I was hardcore into my soldier until finding out that dual-wielding pistols is my best bet. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   They really need to ENHANCE the assault rifles. Played with the trader recently, but you aren't nearly as effective as the NPC ones you fight. They are using Health funnels at 6-10 level that you won't be able to use really until around 15th. Have since started playing with a Martial Artist and missions are a breeze...at least at 6th level. Averaging 15pt hits with martial arts and brawls in the 20's &amp; 30's. Have some very NICE buffs for damage, AC, and martial art skills. Also have a nice personal healing spell that did 41pts the first time I used it. Not bad at 7th level.<br>
<br>
Anyhoo...sorry to ramble. Hope some of this is useful to you.<br>
